<title>HONG KONG: China Resources to set US$250 mln loan.</title>
<headline>China Resources to set US$250 mln loan.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>China Resources Holdings has mandated five banks to arrange a US$250 million loan facility, bankers said.</p>
<p>They said the amortising loan has a final maturity of five years. Repayment is in five semi-annual instalments after three years grace.</p>
<p>It pays an interest margin of 40 basis points over the six-month London Interbank Offered Rate.</p>
<p>The all-in return is expected to be less than 50 basis points, bankers noted.</p>
<p>Proceeds are to be used for refinancing previous debt.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2847 4039</p>
